The paper deals with fault-tolerant distributed computation of aggregate functions in communication networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the use of communication protocols and techniques for improving the resilience of the system, which is related to the sub-category of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). The paper also presents an analysis of the convergence time of the proposed protocol, which is related to the sub-category of Systems and Control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper deals with the processing and manipulation of data, which is related to the sub-category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the accuracy of the proposed protocol and its adjustment using heuristics, which is related to the sub-category of Information Theory (cs.IT).
